VImpressive violin recital
p3
sVnews
p4
VVignana Samithifeatured a fine violin solo by Kamal Kiran Vinjamuri. . This 11-year-old is well acquainted with violin, besides having a good command in Sanskrit, mridangam and karate.Kamal&#8217;s approach was very mature and he possesses good laya. What made it pleasant to sit through his concert was that he thoroughly enjoys playing the instrument with perfecttalam. He hails from a family of musicians and learnt violin from his father Vinjamuri Srinivas Subhash. Currently training under Kanyakumari, Kamal has won several awards.He began his concert with a steady Saveri Varnam and went on to play a brief Shanmukha Priya for Siddhi Vinayakam with swaram kalpana in it.Broche Varueverurain the ragam Khamas of Thyagaraja was neatly rendered followed with a short alap of Arabhi with classy touch of the raga bhavam and then playedRaga sudha rasapanamu chein a fast tempo with flashy swaram. Mohana was chosen forBhavunuthaand was played with great confidence. Kharaharapriya was the key ragam of the day and here Kamal brought the classical sangathis of the raga reflecting the knowledge of the great violin masters of the field. He choseChakkani Rajamargamuthe famous number of Thyagaraja and attempted good neraval atKantiki Sundarauduwith impressive swaram.Kamal concluded his recital with Annamacharya&#8217;sTandanaana, Krishna Nee Begane Baroin Yaman Kalyani of Purandaradasa followed byKurai onrumillaia raga malika and finallyUyyala lugavayya. He displayed the right approach and his attitude towards this highly complex art is noteworthy..
